Romania â€™s central bank is expanding
the list of assets it will accept as collateral in open-market
operations.  Banca Nationala a Romaniei  will accept euro-denominated
bonds issued by Romania on international markets and leu-
denominated bonds issued by global financial institutions from
Oct. 3, the Bucharest-based bank said today in an e-mailed
statement. A margin of 8 percent will deducted from the market
value of eligible securities, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
